OL,3,CLondon Eye breaks down, leaving
OL,4,Cpassengers stuck 135 metres in the air
OL,6,FThe incident was first reported by
OL,7,FMetro newspaper journalist Jen Mills
OL,8,Fwho was stuck in a capsule with her
OL,9,Ffamily when the wheel stopped moving.
OL,11,FShe told Metro: "It got really hot and
OL,12,Fmy son started sweating and crying.
OL,14,F"I got scared too. When you are at the
OL,15,Ftop it is quite scary."
OL,17,F"The capsule became stifling hot and
OL,18,Fbudged forward a few metres before
OL,19,Fpausing again."
